\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"its history\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"its attachment\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"universal human rights\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"our natural tendency\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"Herrero\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Games are set to kick off with an unprecedented parade on the Seine that will see 6,000-7,000 athletes sail six kilometres down the river on a flotilla of boats.\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999741380637, \"rank\": 2.5215120416555477e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paris Games\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"an unprecedented parade\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"6,000-7,000 athletes\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"a flotilla\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"boats\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1163}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Slimani, the Franco-Moroccan author of \\\"Lullaby\\\", a book about a killer nanny, called it a \\\"huge honour\\\" to be asked to take part having arrived in France as an 18-year-old.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1166, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Slimani\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\"}, {\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9775728019482911, \"rank\": 0.022809254742946077, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Franco-Moroccan author\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Lullaby\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1213}, {\"ngram\": \"a book\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"a killer nanny\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1243}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"huge honour\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1295}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She promised \\\"joy, emulation, movement, excitement and sparkle, and not only those famous philosophical values that France displays sometimes with a bit too much self-assurance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9775728019482911, \"rank\": 0.022809254742946077, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"emulation\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"movement\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"excitement\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"sparkle\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"not only those famous philosophical values\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"a bit too much self-assurance\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historian and author Patrick Boucheron, another member of the creative team drafted in by Jolly, said the Paris ceremony would be nothing like the spectacular parade see